## During execution (rules)

- **Append-only timeline.** Never rewrite earlier timeline entries â€” add new ones with a later timestamp.
- **Update the plan's task checklist** in `vault/plans/<slug>.md` as items close. Don't delete unchecked items â€” strike them or move them to Follow-ups.
- **One ADR per hard-to-reverse decision** taken mid-execute. Use `vault/templates/adr.md`. Link from this session and from `vault/decisions/_index.md`.
- **Verify before claiming done.** Run tests, lint, build, or whatever the plan's acceptance criteria specify. Paste evidence into Tests & verification.
- **Do not silently change scope.** If you must, log it under Decisions made mid-flight and ping the user.

## Done criteria (close the phase)

- All in-scope acceptance criteria ticked with evidence, OR explicitly marked deferred under Follow-ups
- Plan note status updated to `done` (or `superseded` if scope drifted hard)
- This session's status set to `done`
- End-of-session summary written
- Feature note (if any) status updated: `done` or back to `active` with remaining tasks
- `vault/index.md` log updated with one line pointing at this session

## Hand-off

When execution closes, say to the user:
> Execution closed: `vault/sessions/<YYYY-MM-DD>-<slug>.md`. Plan `done`. <N> follow-ups logged.

Offer next actions: open the PR, run a wider test pass, or start a new Research phase for follow-ups.

## Behavior in chat

- Edit files directly; do not paste large code blobs into chat that the user must reapply
- After substantial edits, summarize what changed in one paragraph plus the file list â€” do not re-narrate every diff
- If something breaks the plan's gate (e.g., a risk's "trigger to abort" fires), stop and tell the user before continuing
